I probably should have said &#39;empty representation&#39; instead of &#39;empty body&#39;.

So, assuming you have:

==&gt; GET /cache
&lt;== 
&lt;collection&gt;
  &lt;entry&gt;&lt;name&gt;key1&lt;/name&gt;&lt;value&gt;value1&lt;/value&gt;&lt;/entry&gt;
  &lt;entry&gt;&lt;name&gt;key2&lt;/name&gt;&lt;value&gt;value2&lt;/value&gt;&lt;/entry&gt;
&lt;/collection&gt;

and you can do:
==&gt; GET /cache/key1
&lt;==   
&lt;entry&gt;&lt;name&gt;key1&lt;/name&gt;&lt;value&gt;value1&lt;/value&gt;&lt;/entry&gt;

then a reasonable interpretation of PUT would allow it to be used to
clear up the cache:

==&gt; PUT /cache
&lt;collection&gt;&lt;/collection&gt;
&lt;== 204



